WEBVTT

00:02.120 --> 00:05.170
Meredith: Voltaire said
that the art of medicine

00:05.170 --> 00:09.420
is amusing the patient while
nature cures the disease.

00:09.420 --> 00:11.420
So according to one
of the greatest

00:11.420 --> 00:13.250
French philosophers
of all time,

00:13.250 --> 00:15.620
surgeons aren't
really helpers.

00:15.620 --> 00:18.670
♪ Black tears on my shirt ♪
We're more like
circus clowns.

00:18.670 --> 00:22.170
Sorry. Just...
♪ Black tears on my freckles ♪

00:22.170 --> 00:24.170
I know.
♪ I been stung by this hurt ♪

00:24.170 --> 00:26.290
But suck it up,
because I need your help.

00:26.290 --> 00:27.790
♪ I been stung by
the stinging nettle ♪

00:27.790 --> 00:29.960
♪ Someone call, someone call,
some-one call ♪

00:29.960 --> 00:32.000
But help comes in many forms.

00:32.000 --> 00:33.880
I stopped pulling
on my fingers.

00:33.880 --> 00:35.580
Or...
♪ I don't know
who I am at all ♪

00:35.580 --> 00:38.290
...no, a-at least now
I notice when I'm doing it.

00:38.290 --> 00:41.750
[ Chuckles ] And I've been doing
the exercises you showed me.

00:41.750 --> 00:44.000
♪ Someone call, someone call,
some-one call ♪

00:44.000 --> 00:45.790
I'm really noticing
a change.

00:45.790 --> 00:47.540
Don't try to rush it.
♪ I don't know
who I am at all ♪

00:47.540 --> 00:49.250
Takes time for the meds
to balance out.

00:49.250 --> 00:54.330
Right. But...
♪ Black hole in my heart ♪

00:54.330 --> 00:56.120
...well, for instance, uh,
you have a little bit of, um...

00:56.120 --> 00:58.170
♪ Black hole
in my favorite sweater ♪
...I think,

00:58.170 --> 01:01.580
maybe yogurt
on your, uh, chin.

01:01.580 --> 01:03.880
I've wanted to mention it
this whole time,

01:03.880 --> 01:05.210
but I didn't, so...

01:05.210 --> 01:06.710
♪ Someone call, someone call,
some-one call ♪

01:06.710 --> 01:08.290
...I think
we're making progress.

01:08.290 --> 01:11.790
And something tells me
Voltaire never held an aorta

01:11.790 --> 01:13.710
while a patient's
entire blood volume

01:13.710 --> 01:15.880
pulsated between his fingers.

01:15.880 --> 01:17.250
I'd say we are.

01:17.250 --> 01:19.750
♪ Someone call, someone call,
some-one call ♪

01:19.750 --> 01:21.920
You beat up the bar
with a baseball bat?

01:21.920 --> 01:23.960
[ Both laugh ]

01:23.960 --> 01:25.620
♪ I don't know
who I am at all ♪
Not exactly sober behavior.

01:25.620 --> 01:26.880
No.

01:26.880 --> 01:30.080
Legendary,
but definitely not sober.

01:30.080 --> 01:33.170
♪ Hey, hey, hey ♪
And, um, my wife has...

01:33.170 --> 01:35.040
♪ Can anyone hear
what I'm saying? ♪

01:35.040 --> 01:36.960
She's been diagnosed with
something frightening.

01:36.960 --> 01:38.380
Oh, man.

01:38.380 --> 01:40.960
And you were
with Ollie, right?
Yeah.

01:40.960 --> 01:43.330
So you need a sponsor?

01:43.330 --> 01:44.620
If you'd be willing.

01:44.620 --> 01:46.000
♪ Does anyone hear
what I'm saying? ♪

01:46.000 --> 01:48.210
How you doin' with
prayer and meditation?

01:48.210 --> 01:51.210
Uh...I'm not.
♪ Someone call, someone call,
some-one call ♪

01:51.210 --> 01:54.500
Well, how 'bout
we start there?

01:54.500 --> 01:56.210
Call me tomorrow.

01:56.210 --> 01:59.120
♪ I don't know
who I am at all ♪

01:59.120 --> 02:00.580
♪♪

02:00.580 --> 02:07.080
♪ Someone call, someone call,
some-one call ♪

02:07.080 --> 02:10.960
♪ I don't know
who I am at all ♪

02:10.960 --> 02:12.710
[ Elevator bell dings ]

02:12.710 --> 02:13.830
[ Sniffs ]

02:13.830 --> 02:15.620
Oh! Dr. Bailey.

02:15.620 --> 02:17.250
Just the person
I was looking for.

02:17.250 --> 02:19.290
Uh, do you live here now,

02:19.290 --> 02:20.790
or do you fly back
[chuckling] from Germany

02:20.790 --> 02:22.500
on a weekly basis,

02:22.500 --> 02:24.330
and if so, why?

02:24.330 --> 02:25.580
Oh.

02:25.580 --> 02:27.040
Well, um...

02:27.040 --> 02:29.210
I mean,
as it turns out...

02:29.210 --> 02:30.790
I am pregnant.
[ Gasps ]

02:30.790 --> 02:33.040
With Owen's baby.

02:33.040 --> 02:35.540
And Owen and Amelia Shepherd
are back together again,

02:35.540 --> 02:39.250
and Amelia's sisters
have issues with me.

02:39.250 --> 02:41.580
Rightfully so.
It -- It's not undramatic.

02:41.580 --> 02:43.620
It's not undramatic to
the point of it being comical.

02:43.620 --> 02:46.290
And -- And, still,
Dr. Bailey,

02:46.290 --> 02:49.250
I need a job.
I really need a job.

02:49.250 --> 02:51.040
I-I-I need to be occupied
with work,

02:51.040 --> 02:53.170
and I -- I need it badly.

02:53.170 --> 02:54.790
[ Breathes sharply ]

02:54.790 --> 02:56.250
Oh, I'm so sorry.

02:56.250 --> 02:58.120
Um, y-you're gonna
have to say

02:58.120 --> 03:00.120
all of that again
to Alex Karev.

03:01.620 --> 03:03.000
[ Footsteps ]

03:03.000 --> 03:04.290
[ Sighs ]

03:04.290 --> 03:08.170
♪♪

03:08.170 --> 03:10.210
You're on the board?
Yeah. I-I'm sorry.

03:10.210 --> 03:11.460
I want to be there when --

03:11.460 --> 03:13.170
No, no, I have
a dozen little kids

03:13.170 --> 03:14.460
coming to my house
in a few hours.

03:14.460 --> 03:15.880
You said you would help.

03:15.880 --> 03:17.880
I don't know anything
about superheroes.

03:17.880 --> 03:20.670
Well, you tell Bailey that
Uncle Alex is saving lives,

03:20.670 --> 03:22.710
that he actually
is a superhero.

03:22.710 --> 03:24.380
Yeah, right.
That'll definitely work.

03:24.380 --> 03:26.040
Ooh, Dr. Karev,
can I walk with you?

03:26.040 --> 03:27.960
Um, yeah, what,
do you live here?

03:27.960 --> 03:29.460
Well, it's --
it's complicated.

03:29.460 --> 03:30.710
Catherine!
You're back.

03:30.710 --> 03:32.750
How are you feeling?
How am I feeling?

03:32.750 --> 03:34.040
Why don't you tell me?

03:34.040 --> 03:35.540
Since you seem to be
so good

03:35.540 --> 03:37.670
at telling everybody
everything.

03:37.670 --> 03:40.080
Catherine, I --
Save it.

03:40.080 --> 03:41.750
You're fired from my team,
Dr. Grey.

03:41.750 --> 03:44.380
And if you value your job
at this hospital,

03:44.380 --> 03:46.460
I suggest you stay
out of my sight

03:46.460 --> 03:48.380
until my fury passes.

03:48.380 --> 03:53.170
♪♪

03:53.170 --> 03:56.080
[ Indistinct conversations ]

03:56.080 --> 03:58.000
-Hey.
-Hey.

03:58.000 --> 03:59.580
You look nice.

03:59.580 --> 04:01.580
Thanks.
Cece's funeral.

04:01.580 --> 04:03.210
Yes. How'd that go?

04:03.210 --> 04:04.750
It was awful.

04:04.750 --> 04:06.420
And beautiful.

04:06.420 --> 04:08.210
A lot of her single clients
were there.

04:08.210 --> 04:09.960
There will probably be
a lot of hookups tonight.

04:09.960 --> 04:11.670
Fitting.
Yeah.

04:11.670 --> 04:13.170
How are you doing?

04:13.170 --> 04:15.080
Did you talk to your mom?
Uh, yeah.

04:15.080 --> 04:17.380
Yeah, I mean, we all
had dinner last night,

04:17.380 --> 04:19.580
and we all have a surgery
together today, so...

04:19.580 --> 04:22.330
You're doing a surgery?
Catherine's doing a surgery?

04:22.330 --> 04:26.210
A pelvic exenteration that
spares the uterus, to be exact.

04:26.210 --> 04:27.830
And the patient's
ready for us.

04:27.830 --> 04:29.290
-Mm.
-All right.

04:29.290 --> 04:31.170
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Berjeron to the ICU.

04:31.170 --> 04:34.210
Dr. Berjeron to the ICU.

04:34.210 --> 04:36.080
[ Doors slide open ]

04:36.080 --> 04:37.710
[ Siren wails in distance ]

04:37.710 --> 04:40.750
[ Indistinct conversations ]

04:40.750 --> 04:42.250
Morning, Grey.

04:42.250 --> 04:44.250
There's a trauma
coming in.

04:44.250 --> 04:47.170
Yeah, that's why
I'm here.

04:47.170 --> 04:48.790
[ Chuckling ] That's how
you wait for a trauma?

04:48.790 --> 04:51.250
[ Crunching ]
How'm I supposed to wait?

04:51.250 --> 04:53.960
I don't know.
Maybe a little less casually.

04:53.960 --> 04:55.330
So...

04:55.330 --> 04:56.500
[ Crunching ]

04:56.500 --> 04:57.670
Like, uh...

04:57.670 --> 04:59.830
[ Sighs ]

04:59.830 --> 05:02.120
Yeah.
[ Laughs ]

05:02.120 --> 05:04.540
Hey, where's the rig?

05:04.540 --> 05:05.460
It's not here yet.

05:05.460 --> 05:06.710
See?

05:06.710 --> 05:08.250
Jo knows how to wait
for a trauma.

05:08.250 --> 05:10.540
No point in stressing out
until you have to.

05:10.540 --> 05:11.790
I don't believe in that.

05:11.790 --> 05:13.210
You don't believe in that?

05:13.210 --> 05:15.250
Mnh-mnh.
[ Siren approaches ]

05:18.170 --> 05:19.790
And now
I stand up straight.

05:19.790 --> 05:22.210
[ Siren wailing ]

05:25.120 --> 05:26.830
[ Wailing continues ]

05:26.830 --> 05:29.080
[ Brakes screech ]

05:29.080 --> 05:31.040
[ Groans, sniffles ]

05:32.420 --> 05:33.750
-Hey.
-Hey.

05:33.750 --> 05:35.000
You look awful.

05:35.000 --> 05:36.170
[ Chuckles ]
Thanks.

05:36.170 --> 05:37.920
No, I mean, you should
go home if you're sick.

05:37.920 --> 05:40.540
Uh. Pit's full of people who
look a lot worse than I do.

05:40.540 --> 05:42.040
Yeah, flu season.
Yeah.

05:43.170 --> 05:44.460
You're in scrubs?

05:44.460 --> 05:45.830
Yeah.

05:45.830 --> 05:47.120
I have to audition
for Pierce,

05:47.120 --> 05:49.290
which is only
slightly enraging.

05:49.290 --> 05:51.500
Did you know that Alex Karev
is interim chief?

05:51.500 --> 05:53.290
I mean, time is so weird.

05:53.290 --> 05:54.830
So, you're gonna work here?

05:56.330 --> 05:58.210
And I find out
after the fact.

05:58.210 --> 05:59.290
[ Chuckles ]

05:59.290 --> 06:00.380
That's par
for the course.

06:00.380 --> 06:01.710
Whoa, whoa,
wait a minute.

06:01.710 --> 06:03.880
Where is this
coming from?
[ Sighs ]

06:03.880 --> 06:05.460
You said that you wanted
to figure it out,

06:05.460 --> 06:06.960
and that's what
I'm trying to do.

06:06.960 --> 06:08.380
Yeah, me, too, but there's
a lot to figure out.

06:08.380 --> 06:10.500
And this whole situation
is a mess.

06:10.500 --> 06:12.710
Okay, let me remind you
that the reason

06:12.710 --> 06:15.040
I upended my entire life
was for you

06:15.040 --> 06:16.380
so that you could be part
of our baby's life.

06:16.380 --> 06:17.380
Listen, Teddy,
you came to Seattle

06:17.380 --> 06:18.880
the day
after Karev's wedding,

06:18.880 --> 06:20.000
before me and Amelia

06:20.000 --> 06:21.170
had even really
gotten back together.

06:21.170 --> 06:22.880
You seemed pretty
back together to me.

06:22.880 --> 06:24.380
Right, right,
and you took one look,

06:24.380 --> 06:26.040
and you decided that
you had the whole picture.

06:26.040 --> 06:27.540
Maybe if you'd
just talked to me,

06:27.540 --> 06:29.000
been a little more
up front with me...

06:29.000 --> 06:30.880
Your teenager
answered your door!

06:30.880 --> 06:33.120
...maybe you would've saved
a lot of people a lot of pain,

06:33.120 --> 06:34.960
but, no, you waited
five whole weeks to --

06:34.960 --> 06:36.790
Wait, are you try--
A-Are you saying that somehow

06:36.790 --> 06:38.500
it's my fault that you and
Amelia are back together again?

06:38.500 --> 06:40.170
I'm just saying
it's a crap situation,

06:40.170 --> 06:41.250
which is worse
than it would have been

06:41.250 --> 06:42.580
had you been
a little more up front.

06:42.580 --> 06:44.540
Had some
excellent nicknames,

06:44.540 --> 06:47.620
but "Crap Situation"
might be my new favorite.

06:47.620 --> 06:50.960
♪♪

06:50.960 --> 06:52.170
Amelia.

06:52.170 --> 06:54.080
Hey, Amelia, I'm sorry.

06:54.080 --> 06:56.620
[ Keys clacking lightly ]

06:56.620 --> 06:58.880
♪♪

06:58.880 --> 07:00.580
Hey.

07:00.580 --> 07:01.960
So...

07:02.960 --> 07:05.290
I need a job.

07:05.290 --> 07:07.500
And Karev said that
I should talk to you.

07:07.500 --> 07:11.460
♪♪

07:23.120 --> 07:25.120
Her abdomen's distended. She may
have some internal bleeding.

07:25.120 --> 07:26.420
Let's get an ultrasound.

07:26.420 --> 07:28.170
Let's hang some LR
and a unit of O-neg.

07:28.170 --> 07:29.710
She fell from
a hotel balcony?

07:29.710 --> 07:32.290
Three floors up.
Apparently the railing broke.

07:32.290 --> 07:35.290
Pelvis feels stable,
but I want to see an X-ray.
Yes, Dr. Lincoln.

07:35.290 --> 07:36.710
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God!

07:36.710 --> 07:39.080
Natasha, I'm right here.

07:39.080 --> 07:41.380
I'm right here.
Oh, my God.

07:41.380 --> 07:43.210
Oh, my God. Is she --

07:43.210 --> 07:44.880
Is she
on any medications?

07:44.880 --> 07:46.500
Has she had
any previous surgeries?

07:46.500 --> 07:49.500
Um...uh, she -- she gets
migraines sometimes, and --

07:49.500 --> 07:51.790
and she has a scar from --
she had her appendix out.

07:51.790 --> 07:55.210
Is -- Is she -- I'm --

07:55.210 --> 07:57.040
We're getting married
tomorrow.

07:57.040 --> 07:59.000
She didn't want me to see her
until she walked down the aisle,

07:59.000 --> 08:01.420
and I --
she got her own hotel room.

08:01.420 --> 08:03.670
Hey, hey, hey.
What's your name, buddy?

08:03.670 --> 08:05.670
Garrett...Boland.

08:05.670 --> 08:08.170
Garrett. Okay, well, the best
thing you can do to help Natasha

08:08.170 --> 08:09.420
is to let the people
in this room

08:09.420 --> 08:10.540
do what we know
how to do, okay?

08:10.540 --> 08:12.290
Okay, okay.
Oh, God.

08:12.290 --> 08:13.960
Nurse: Let me show you
where to wait.

08:13.960 --> 08:16.120
And I thought my wedding day
was a mess.

08:17.420 --> 08:19.080
I'm sorry
I said that, Amelia.

08:19.080 --> 08:21.120
We were fighting,
and it just --
It happens.

08:21.120 --> 08:22.250
Couples fight.

08:22.250 --> 08:23.670
Oh, come on.
We're not a couple.

08:23.670 --> 08:24.790
Who's not a couple?

08:24.790 --> 08:27.210
Owen and Teddy Altman.
Only they are.

08:27.210 --> 08:28.500
The baby really sells it.

08:28.500 --> 08:29.880
Oh, there's a baby?

08:29.880 --> 08:31.290
Do you mind?
[ Coughs ]

08:31.290 --> 08:32.880
You know, I do, actually.
We're busy.

08:32.880 --> 08:34.290
Way too busy
to catch whatever it is

08:34.290 --> 08:37.880
you're losing a fight against,
so...you can go.

08:37.880 --> 08:39.960
Amelia, please.
Owen, he's right.

08:39.960 --> 08:41.500
We're going up against
one of the nastiest tumors

08:41.500 --> 08:43.960
I've ever seen.
We need to focus.

08:43.960 --> 08:46.960
[ Exhales sharply,
coughs ]

08:46.960 --> 08:48.500
Altman's the tall
blonde, right?

08:48.500 --> 08:51.460
I am trying to focus.
[ Sighs ]

08:53.000 --> 08:56.540
Uma Paxton, 25, here for
total pelvic exenteration

08:56.540 --> 09:00.170
with flap reconstruction
for a recurrent vaginal tumor.

09:00.170 --> 09:01.670
Not total, Dr. Helm.

09:01.670 --> 09:03.750
We are preserving
the uterus.

09:03.750 --> 09:04.920
Oh.

09:04.920 --> 09:06.250
Wow, that's possible?

09:06.250 --> 09:07.460
It is now.

09:07.460 --> 09:09.540
Because I developed
the technique.

09:09.540 --> 09:12.120
My first doctors blasted me
with chemo and radiation,

09:12.120 --> 09:14.080
but it came back,

09:14.080 --> 09:17.000
so they said I had to remove
most of my insides,

09:17.000 --> 09:20.380
but Dr. Fox
found a silver lining.

09:20.380 --> 09:21.960
-Dr. Webber?
-I'll make an incision

09:21.960 --> 09:24.290
into your abdomen
and remove your rectum

09:24.290 --> 09:26.250
to create a colostomy

09:26.250 --> 09:28.120
while Dr. Fox
removes your bladder

09:28.120 --> 09:29.580
and creates a urostomy.

09:29.580 --> 09:31.040
And then
I will remove the tumor

09:31.040 --> 09:33.330
and everything
but your uterus.

09:33.330 --> 09:35.000
I'll lead on
your vaginal reconstruction.

09:35.000 --> 09:37.790
We'll cover any defects with
skin and fat from your belly.

09:37.790 --> 09:39.670
So...
not complicated.

09:39.670 --> 09:41.880
[ All chuckle ]

09:41.880 --> 09:44.000
Man, I didn't think
that I ever wanted kids

09:44.000 --> 09:46.580
until I found out that I might
not be able to have any,

09:46.580 --> 09:50.540
so thank you, Dr. Fox.

09:50.540 --> 09:53.040
Uma, we've talked
about this before,

09:53.040 --> 09:54.960
but now that
the day has come,

09:54.960 --> 09:57.040
I really have to ask again.

09:57.040 --> 09:59.250
This surgery's long,
it's complex,

09:59.250 --> 10:01.080
and it's very personal.

10:01.080 --> 10:03.000
Are you sure you're all right
with other doctors

10:03.000 --> 10:05.460
watching from the gallery?

10:05.460 --> 10:07.460
You're a pioneer,

10:07.460 --> 10:10.670
and this could help save
more women like me.

10:10.670 --> 10:13.460
So teach away.

10:13.460 --> 10:15.540
All right, guys.
Let's do this.

10:15.540 --> 10:16.790
[ Chuckles ]

10:19.250 --> 10:22.080
[ Coughing ]
DeLuca: I'm gonna be
right back, all right?

10:22.080 --> 10:23.580
It's like
a plague in here.

10:23.580 --> 10:25.420
Bronchitis, pneumonia,
some gastroenteritis.

10:25.420 --> 10:26.750
[ Sneezes ]

10:26.750 --> 10:27.790
Whoa, you okay?

10:27.790 --> 10:29.420
Ohh. What do we got?

10:29.420 --> 10:31.080
Right. Uh, Grey and Link
are in Trauma 2

10:31.080 --> 10:32.330
with a woman
who fell from a balcony,

10:32.330 --> 10:34.330
and almost everyone else
is flu-like symptoms.

10:34.330 --> 10:36.790
[ Coughing ]
Including you, I guess.

10:36.790 --> 10:38.000
Look, if you want
to grab some rest,

10:38.000 --> 10:39.210
I can page you
if anything's urgent.

10:39.210 --> 10:40.540
-Incoming!
-Uh -- Ohh.

10:40.540 --> 10:42.250
-Sorry! Sorry! Sorry!
-I'm gonna muscle through.

10:42.250 --> 10:44.080
Could you, uh,
prep an IV, uh,

10:44.080 --> 10:46.080
bag of LR
and 4 milligrams of Zofran?

10:46.080 --> 10:48.250
Yeah. You got it.
Thanks.

10:48.250 --> 10:49.670
So, we have our
interdepartmental meetings,

10:49.670 --> 10:51.880
M&Ms, lung tumor boards,
and such

10:51.880 --> 10:52.960
in the conference room.

10:52.960 --> 10:54.380
Oh, good,
you still do it there.

10:54.380 --> 10:55.830
I-I moved it
from the lecture hall

10:55.830 --> 10:58.210
to get a more open
and honest exchange.

10:58.210 --> 11:00.290
"A more open
and honest exchange."

11:00.290 --> 11:02.330
You don't say.

11:02.330 --> 11:04.500
Well, it's just that my sister's
kinda wrecked right now

11:04.500 --> 11:06.670
because you failed to have
an open and honest exchange.

11:06.670 --> 11:07.830
I told them.

11:07.830 --> 11:10.080
You told them too late.

11:10.080 --> 11:12.040
[ Sighs ]

11:12.040 --> 11:15.380
Are we gonna be able to
work together, Dr. Pierce?

11:15.380 --> 11:16.500
[ Sighs ]

11:17.830 --> 11:20.290
I've heard nothing but excellent
things about your work,

11:20.290 --> 11:22.290
Dr. Altman,
and any minute now,

11:22.290 --> 11:25.080
I will shove aside
my personal contempt

11:25.080 --> 11:27.460
in favor of
professional courtesy.

11:27.460 --> 11:29.380
Woman on P.A.: Dr. Huser
to Labor and Delivery.

11:29.380 --> 11:31.120
Dr. Huser
to Labor and Delivery.

11:31.120 --> 11:32.120
[ Sighs deeply ]

11:32.120 --> 11:34.420
On 3 -- 1, 2, 3.
What do we got?

11:34.420 --> 11:36.000
Patient collapsed
at a convenience store.

11:36.000 --> 11:38.420
Last BP 110 over 50,
pulse 82.

11:38.420 --> 11:40.040
Ma'am, did you
lose consciousness?

11:40.040 --> 11:42.080
Uh, no,
I don't think so.

11:42.080 --> 11:43.460
Hey, guys,
what did you see?

11:43.460 --> 11:45.830
She was like,
"Ow, my stomach."

11:45.830 --> 11:47.880
Then she was like,
"Ow, my face."

11:47.880 --> 11:49.330
-[ Chuckles ]
-Nice, guys. Real nice.

11:49.330 --> 11:50.880
Ma'am, do you have
any other symptoms

11:50.880 --> 11:52.380
uh, dizziness or headache?

11:52.380 --> 11:55.330
Uh, yeah, headache because
Gabe just told me today

11:55.330 --> 11:57.120
that his project
is due tomorrow...

11:57.120 --> 11:58.580
-Quit touching me!
-You touched me first!

11:58.580 --> 12:00.250
...and I have the flu,
and I hate children,

12:00.250 --> 12:02.040
so life is punishing me.
Eli: No! Let me go!

12:02.040 --> 12:04.290
So if I could just get
something for my stomach

12:04.290 --> 12:05.790
and some sedatives
for the children...
Let me go!

12:05.790 --> 12:06.670
-...we'll be good to go.
-Hey, watch out.

12:06.670 --> 12:08.500
Hey, guys, guys,
knock it off.

12:08.500 --> 12:09.750
Should we call
their parents?

12:09.750 --> 12:11.500
I am their parents...
Eli: It's your fault!

12:11.500 --> 12:13.330
...ever since
my sister died,

12:13.330 --> 12:15.170
and clearly,
I'm crushing it -- Ow!

12:15.170 --> 12:16.540
Abdomen's a little tender.

12:16.540 --> 12:18.040
Uh, Schmitt, do you want
to see if CT's open?

12:18.040 --> 12:19.670
Whoa, CT?
No, no, I'm fine.

12:19.670 --> 12:22.290
I just have the flu,
and I already took antibiotics

12:22.290 --> 12:24.080
I had left over
from last year, so...

12:24.080 --> 12:25.790
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

12:25.790 --> 12:26.830
Bad idea?

12:26.830 --> 12:28.710
Unprescribed?
Yes.

12:28.710 --> 12:30.250
Listen, I know
that you're stressed,

12:30.250 --> 12:32.170
and maybe it is
just the flu, but...

12:32.170 --> 12:33.330
Claire, if it isn't,

12:33.330 --> 12:36.920
you're really gonna wish
that you'd stayed, okay?

12:36.920 --> 12:38.330
Are you okay?

12:38.330 --> 12:40.580
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, I'm fine.

12:40.580 --> 12:42.120
[ Clears throat ]
He sounds like me.

12:42.120 --> 12:43.420
[ Chuckles ]

12:44.580 --> 12:47.580
Free fluid in the pelvis
and abdomen.

12:47.580 --> 12:48.670
Casey: X-rays are up.

12:48.670 --> 12:50.500
Post-ops are done, Link.
What'd I miss?

12:50.500 --> 12:52.120
You tell me.

12:52.120 --> 12:54.250
She's got
a windswept pelvis.

12:54.250 --> 12:56.290
"Windswept"?
It's a combo platter.

12:56.290 --> 12:57.210
We got AP compression
on one side,

12:57.210 --> 12:59.040
lateral compression
on the other.

12:59.040 --> 13:00.620
You see the widened
SI joint here

13:00.620 --> 13:02.040
and the sacral fracture
there?

13:02.040 --> 13:03.120
Meredith: Okay, well, I'd love
to get her up to the O.R.

13:03.120 --> 13:04.460
for a neuro check.

13:04.460 --> 13:06.330
And we can do an intra-op CT
when we get there.

13:06.330 --> 13:07.830
100%. Let's do it.

13:07.830 --> 13:09.500
Well, wait, aren't we gonna
stabilize her pelvis first?

13:09.500 --> 13:11.170
Of course.
Nah.

13:11.170 --> 13:12.460
"Nah"? She's got
a pelvic fracture.

13:12.460 --> 13:13.670
You're not gonna at least
put a binder on her?

13:13.670 --> 13:15.250
Nope.
We'll see you up there.

13:15.250 --> 13:17.710
♪♪

13:17.710 --> 13:18.710
[ Alarm blaring ]

13:18.710 --> 13:19.960
All right.
She's hypotensive.

13:19.960 --> 13:21.710
We got to move, people.

13:30.710 --> 13:32.420
Jo: She's all prepped
for her ex-lap.

13:32.420 --> 13:34.040
Okay, so what
made you think

13:34.040 --> 13:36.620
that Link and I
would be a good match?

13:36.620 --> 13:38.460
Okay, listen,
before I met Alex,

13:38.460 --> 13:40.500
Link was the very best person
that I knew,

13:40.500 --> 13:43.750
and Alex would say the
same thing about you, so...

13:43.750 --> 13:46.210
[ Laughing ] Oh, come on.
Link's a great guy.

13:46.210 --> 13:47.960
And Labradors
are great dogs.

13:47.960 --> 13:49.380
They're always
happy to see you,

13:49.380 --> 13:50.880
they're super cute,
and they're full of energy.

13:50.880 --> 13:52.580
Okay, listen.
He is not a Labrador.

13:52.580 --> 13:54.960
You just have to
get to know him.

13:54.960 --> 13:56.880
[ Door opens, closes ]
[ Panting ]

13:56.880 --> 13:59.170
Who's ready to put
a pelvis back together, huh?

13:59.170 --> 14:00.540
I am.

14:00.540 --> 14:02.080
I am ready.

14:02.080 --> 14:03.420
[ Water running ]

14:03.420 --> 14:04.960
Did you jog up here?

14:04.960 --> 14:07.540
Ran up the stairs. Gets the
blood flowing, you know?

14:07.540 --> 14:09.290
We got to save this lady.
She's getting married.

14:09.290 --> 14:12.080
We have to save them all,
even the sad and lonely ones.

14:15.620 --> 14:19.710
Is there another Dr. Grey
you thought I should ask out?

14:19.710 --> 14:21.120
[ Sighs ]

14:22.170 --> 14:24.790
Okay, just relax
and try not to move, okay?

14:24.790 --> 14:27.790
[ Sighs ] I haven't relaxed
in two years.

14:27.790 --> 14:29.540
My mother used to say, "I hope
you have children someday,

14:29.540 --> 14:32.040
and they're as awful to you
as you were to me."

14:32.040 --> 14:33.830
And I'd say,
"Joke's on you, lady.

14:33.830 --> 14:35.170
I'm never having kids."

14:35.170 --> 14:36.420
And then Cynthia died,

14:36.420 --> 14:40.080
and now I have
her two human tornadoes.

14:40.080 --> 14:42.000
They're loud,
and they're smelly,

14:42.000 --> 14:44.210
and they think
fart jokes are hilarious,

14:44.210 --> 14:46.120
and they never stop eating.

14:47.380 --> 14:51.460
I love them,
but they are disgusting.

14:51.460 --> 14:53.040
I think I owe my mom
an apology.

14:53.040 --> 14:54.420
Yeah, me too.

14:54.420 --> 14:55.580
Whoa.

14:55.580 --> 14:57.540
Her transverse colon is --
is huge.

14:57.540 --> 15:00.500
Toxic megacolon
with peritoneal signs.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.750
We're gonna need to
get her to the O.R.

15:01.750 --> 15:04.210
before her bowel perfs,
okay?

15:04.210 --> 15:05.750
I was hoping,
if we start medially,

15:05.750 --> 15:07.290
we could remove the tumor
en bloc.

15:07.290 --> 15:08.420
[ Rapid beeping ]

15:08.420 --> 15:10.210
Ah...
It's not working.

15:10.210 --> 15:11.460
I know. Just...

15:11.460 --> 15:13.960
Let's try coming
from the inferior side.

15:13.960 --> 15:15.880
Maybe if you approach it
superiorly --

15:15.880 --> 15:17.170
I am.

15:19.460 --> 15:20.670
[ Sighs ] Yeah,
it's still not working.

15:20.670 --> 15:22.290
You know,
I can see that, Shepherd.

15:22.290 --> 15:23.540
That's why
we're practicing.

15:23.540 --> 15:24.790
And at this rate,
we will be ready

15:24.790 --> 15:26.500
in, what --
five years?

15:26.500 --> 15:28.580
Don't take your baby daddy drama
out on our tumor baby.

15:28.580 --> 15:30.500
We can do this.

15:30.500 --> 15:33.540
[ Cellphone chimes, vibrates ]

15:33.540 --> 15:35.420
Consult in the O.R.
I'll be right back.

15:35.420 --> 15:37.880
Wh-What -- You're --
You're leaving?

15:37.880 --> 15:41.750
Do me a favor and come back
with a little positivity!

15:41.750 --> 15:43.040
[ Sighing ]

15:43.040 --> 15:44.830
[ Door slides shut ]

15:47.120 --> 15:49.120
[ Indistinct conversations ]

15:49.120 --> 15:51.830
[ Monitor beeping ]

15:51.830 --> 15:52.880
It's quite a crowd.

15:52.880 --> 15:55.540
[ Chuckles ]
Quite a surgery.

15:55.540 --> 15:57.790
It sounds really complicated.
I hope it goes well.

15:57.790 --> 16:01.540
Well, if you thought you might
be performing your last surgery,

16:01.540 --> 16:03.330
wouldn't you want to
go out with a bang?

16:03.330 --> 16:05.000
Catherine told you?

16:05.000 --> 16:06.210
This morning.

16:06.210 --> 16:08.290
She's symptomatic.
She's in pain.

16:08.290 --> 16:09.960
[ Sighs deeply ]

16:09.960 --> 16:11.210
This is not
a simple surgery.

16:11.210 --> 16:13.120
I mean, do you think
this is a good idea?

16:13.120 --> 16:15.960
I think
she's Catherine Fox.

16:15.960 --> 16:18.290
I think...

16:18.290 --> 16:20.620
she's gonna
make her mark here.

16:20.620 --> 16:24.500
And I think she has
a stellar team by her side.

16:24.500 --> 16:26.080
They're ready.

16:26.080 --> 16:29.380
[ Monitor beeping,
respirator hissing ]

16:29.380 --> 16:31.790
♪♪

16:31.790 --> 16:33.830
Full house.

16:33.830 --> 16:35.120
10 blade.

16:35.120 --> 16:41.540
♪♪

16:41.540 --> 16:43.420
Amelia: No bleed,
no indications for surgery.

16:43.420 --> 16:45.250
Possibly an anoxic
brain injury,

16:45.250 --> 16:47.500
so I'll monitor her closely
in post-op.

16:47.500 --> 16:48.670
Link: Thank you,
Shepherd.

16:48.670 --> 16:49.750
Meredith: Basin.

16:49.750 --> 16:51.960
Spleen is out.

16:51.960 --> 16:53.960
Bleeding in the left-upper
quadrant is controlled,

16:53.960 --> 16:55.580
but it must be coming
from somewhere.

16:55.580 --> 16:57.120
How many units
have we gone through?
Nico: Eleven.

16:57.120 --> 16:58.420
I'm gonna clamp
the internal iliac,

16:58.420 --> 16:59.960
try to slow the bleeding.
-Mm-hmm.

16:59.960 --> 17:01.500
Parker,
just so you're clear,

17:01.500 --> 17:02.750
we would have gone through
fewer units

17:02.750 --> 17:04.620
had we stabilized her
in the E.R.

17:04.620 --> 17:06.250
Yes, Dr. Gray.

17:06.250 --> 17:08.000
-Retraction here, Nico.
-Got it.

17:08.000 --> 17:09.790
A pelvic binder
tamponades the bleeding --

17:09.790 --> 17:11.250
it's a very simple
standard of care.

17:11.250 --> 17:13.290
-Yes, ma'am.
-More retraction.

17:13.290 --> 17:14.670
How did you even
become a doctor

17:14.670 --> 17:17.460
with this sort of "everything'll
work itself out" attitude?

17:17.460 --> 17:19.210
I became a doctor
the way everyone does, Grey.

17:19.210 --> 17:20.830
I worked my ass off,
I went to med school --

17:20.830 --> 17:22.250
He became a doctor
because he got cancer --

17:22.250 --> 17:24.420
Jo, that's not
your story to tell.

17:24.420 --> 17:26.670
Sorry. But he's --
he's not a lightweight,

17:26.670 --> 17:28.620
and he's not an idiot.
Thank you.

17:28.620 --> 17:30.750
Got it.

17:30.750 --> 17:32.540
What? Where?

17:32.540 --> 17:33.830
Check this out, Parker.

17:33.830 --> 17:35.920
You want to make sure
you pack below the pelvic brim.

17:35.920 --> 17:37.290
That's where
you're gonna run into

17:37.290 --> 17:38.670
a lot of the
nasty vascular variants

17:38.670 --> 17:39.830
like the crown of death.

17:39.830 --> 17:41.380
I had a hunch
when I saw the X-ray,

17:41.380 --> 17:43.290
and I typically do use
a pelvic binder,

17:43.290 --> 17:44.540
but in this case,
it could've caused

17:44.540 --> 17:47.210
the internally rotated side
to be crushed inward,

17:47.210 --> 17:48.580
causing
even further damage.

17:48.580 --> 17:51.330
And you couldn't have
just said that in the E.R.?

17:51.330 --> 17:54.380
I guess I could've, but
I didn't realize part of my job

17:54.380 --> 17:55.710
was convincing you
I belonged here.

17:55.710 --> 17:57.830
[ Liquid suctioning ]

17:57.830 --> 17:59.330
I thought
I just had the flu

17:59.330 --> 18:00.920
and the antibiotics
would knock it out.

18:00.920 --> 18:02.250
No, no.
The antibiotics wiped out

18:02.250 --> 18:03.880
the good bacteria
in your intestine,

18:03.880 --> 18:05.000
which caused
severe inflammation

18:05.000 --> 18:06.040
that made you pass out.

18:06.040 --> 18:07.040
But we caught it
just in time.

18:07.040 --> 18:08.330
Just in time?

18:08.330 --> 18:10.210
Like, before it killed me?

18:10.210 --> 18:12.250
Oh, God. I-I --
I-I can't die.

18:12.250 --> 18:14.540
[ Voice breaking ] Those boys
can't lose another parent.

18:14.540 --> 18:15.880
Eli just got to the point

18:15.880 --> 18:17.620
where he's not
crying at night.

18:17.620 --> 18:18.830
They -- They need me.

18:18.830 --> 18:20.250
They need --
[ Screams ]

18:20.250 --> 18:21.540
Okay, the bowel
seems to have ruptured.

18:21.540 --> 18:23.420
Let's, uh, get her
intubated and prepped.

18:23.420 --> 18:24.670
DeLuca:
She's moving too much.

18:24.670 --> 18:26.920
Okay, let's push
100 of propofol with 100 of sux.

18:26.920 --> 18:29.830
-Already on it.
-Good.

18:29.830 --> 18:32.040
What?
I-I -- Oops.

18:32.040 --> 18:33.880
[ Winces ]
Oh, my God.

18:33.880 --> 18:35.080
Oh, God, did you --

18:35.080 --> 18:37.330
I'm so sorry.

18:37.330 --> 18:39.170
Okay, everybody, stop!
Listen to me.

18:39.170 --> 18:41.710
The propofol and sux had just
been accidentally injected

18:41.710 --> 18:43.460
into my IV, which means
I have about 30 seconds

18:43.460 --> 18:44.920
until I will be paralyzed.

18:44.920 --> 18:46.040
So let's page the chief.

18:46.040 --> 18:47.540
DeLuca,
start the surgery, stat.

18:47.540 --> 18:49.000
Uh, I'm gonna need somebody
to put a tube in me,

18:49.000 --> 18:50.580
because once I am down,
I'm gonna lose my airway,

18:50.580 --> 18:52.500
and if I can't breathe,
then I will die.

18:52.500 --> 18:54.540
I'd also appreciate it
if somebody could help me

18:54.540 --> 18:55.920
by breaking my fa--

19:01.960 --> 19:04.290
-Patient's intubated.
-Okay, Schmitt, look at me.

19:04.290 --> 19:05.330
Don't rock
the laryngoscope, okay?

19:05.330 --> 19:06.500
10 blade.

19:06.500 --> 19:09.880
♪♪

19:09.880 --> 19:13.540
Now, drive the tube
in between his vocal chords.

19:13.540 --> 19:16.920
Dr. Hunt, you may experience
some discomfort now.

19:16.920 --> 19:18.790
Schmitt, he can't hear you.
I've never done this.

19:18.790 --> 19:20.080
That doesn't mean
you can't, all right?

19:20.080 --> 19:21.380
Now, Bovie.

19:21.380 --> 19:23.830
♪♪

19:23.830 --> 19:25.620
[ Monitor beeping ]

19:25.620 --> 19:27.880
♪♪

19:27.880 --> 19:30.080
I did it.
I did it!

19:30.080 --> 19:31.790
Okay, do not
stop bagging, okay?

19:31.790 --> 19:33.620
Get him upstairs,
hook him up to some fluids.

19:33.620 --> 19:34.790
Now. Come on.
Let's go.

19:36.420 --> 19:38.170
[ Metal clinks lightly ]

19:40.580 --> 19:41.920
[ Monitor beeping ]

19:41.920 --> 19:44.290
She's in a coma?

19:44.290 --> 19:46.790
It's a
medically induced coma.

19:46.790 --> 19:49.040
The sedation
will keep her calm

19:49.040 --> 19:50.960
and allow her body to heal.

19:50.960 --> 19:52.330
[ Monitor beeping ]

19:52.330 --> 19:54.250
But...

19:54.250 --> 19:55.880
she will wake up?

19:55.880 --> 19:58.420
Natasha lost
a lot of blood,

19:58.420 --> 20:00.750
and her body underwent
severe stress.

20:00.750 --> 20:01.960
We don't always know

20:01.960 --> 20:04.080
how a patient's
gonna recover from that.

20:04.080 --> 20:05.580
So she won't wake up.

20:05.580 --> 20:07.460
We can't know for sure.

20:07.460 --> 20:10.790
We will continue to monitor her
and support her

20:10.790 --> 20:12.080
and do everything we can.

20:14.080 --> 20:16.170
I don't know what to do.

20:16.170 --> 20:18.580
You can hold her hand.
You can speak to her.

20:18.580 --> 20:20.500
She may be able
to hear you.

20:20.500 --> 20:22.620
[ Beeping continues ]

20:24.750 --> 20:27.830
She was gonna wear
a blue dress...

20:27.830 --> 20:29.210
for our wedding.

20:29.210 --> 20:31.670
She's not
a traditionalist, and...

20:31.670 --> 20:34.380
[ Voice breaking ]
...she's not a kid.

20:34.380 --> 20:39.000
We waited forever
to meet each other.

20:39.000 --> 20:42.120
It was just
this one tradition --

20:42.120 --> 20:43.120
sleeping apart.

20:45.540 --> 20:49.250
We thought it would
bring us good luck.

20:49.250 --> 20:51.920
I don't want
to do life without you

20:51.920 --> 20:53.960
now that I know
what it's like with you.

20:56.620 --> 20:59.460
[ Inhales sharply ]

20:59.460 --> 21:01.040
[ Voice breaking ]
Wake up...

21:01.040 --> 21:06.120
♪♪

21:06.120 --> 21:07.750
...and marry me.

21:09.330 --> 21:11.170
[ Sniffles ]

21:12.040 --> 21:13.960
Please.

21:14.790 --> 21:16.830
Please.

21:16.830 --> 21:19.040
[ Crying ]

21:20.210 --> 21:23.670
[ Indistinct conversations ]

21:26.880 --> 21:28.580
What's wrong?

21:28.580 --> 21:32.000
I'm just glad
that you're alive,

21:32.000 --> 21:34.500
glad that we're alive.

21:34.500 --> 21:36.670
Me too.

21:36.670 --> 21:39.250
I have a surgery.
You okay?
Yeah.

21:39.250 --> 21:41.420
Hey, thanks
for marrying me.

21:44.080 --> 21:45.580
You're welcome.

21:46.750 --> 21:48.210
Koracick:
I know, Shepherd. I know.

21:48.210 --> 21:49.460
I've run every one
of those scenarios!

21:49.460 --> 21:51.000
Amelia: I am just trying
to be realistic.

21:51.000 --> 21:52.580
Well, maybe if you'd stop
running off to consults --

21:52.580 --> 21:54.040
That has nothing to do
with the fact

21:54.040 --> 21:55.880
that we are staring down
the impossible here.

21:55.880 --> 21:57.250
Where is
the Amelia Shepherd

21:57.250 --> 21:59.250
that looked at Nicole Herman's
inoperable brain tumor

21:59.250 --> 22:01.380
and said, "Yes, I can,
and I should"?

22:01.380 --> 22:03.080
That was Brain Tumor Amelia.

22:03.080 --> 22:05.790
Non-Brain Tumor Amelia
is a reasonable surgeon

22:05.790 --> 22:07.420
who asks
reasonable questions.

22:07.420 --> 22:09.670
I --
And she is currently speaking
in the third person,

22:09.670 --> 22:12.380
so, you know...

22:12.380 --> 22:13.960
This is what
we are dealing with.

22:13.960 --> 22:15.710
We have to visualize this.

22:15.710 --> 22:17.080
Well, that would be lovely,
but it's not an option.

22:17.080 --> 22:19.000
Yes, it is.

22:19.000 --> 22:20.580
Okay, you guys were
talking really loud,

22:20.580 --> 22:22.170
so I'm not gonna apologize
for eavesdropping

22:22.170 --> 22:23.960
despite your angry faces.

22:23.960 --> 22:25.500
Jo --
No, th-there is a way

22:25.500 --> 22:27.620
to 3-D visualize
a tumor like that.

22:27.620 --> 22:29.210
It's brand-new,
and they're about to do

22:29.210 --> 22:30.790
the first launch of it
at UCSD.

22:30.790 --> 22:32.210
-It's called the ORBEYE.
-Oh.

22:32.210 --> 22:33.500
Can I just see your...

22:33.500 --> 22:35.380
That's -- Yeah, that's fine.
G-Go ahead.

22:37.250 --> 22:38.790
[ Whispering ]
Who is she?

22:38.790 --> 22:41.790
[ Whispering ] She's a surgical
fellow studying future medicine.

22:41.790 --> 22:43.210
That's not a thing.

22:43.210 --> 22:44.880
Uh, am I dreaming,
'cause she, uh,

22:44.880 --> 22:46.080
just walked in
with a miracle,

22:46.080 --> 22:48.330
and she looks like a...
mermaid.

22:48.330 --> 22:49.580
It's still
a giant tumor, Tom.

22:49.580 --> 22:50.830
[ Shushing ]

22:50.830 --> 22:52.710
-Just let me have this.
-Okay.

22:52.710 --> 22:53.830
♪♪

22:53.830 --> 22:55.750
What?

22:55.750 --> 22:58.000
[ Respirator hissing ]

22:58.000 --> 22:59.290
I want him to be on fluids,

22:59.290 --> 23:01.000
and check his vitals
every 15 minutes.

23:01.000 --> 23:03.120
I don't want to miss any bumps
in Dr. Hunt's numbers.

23:03.120 --> 23:05.080
-Of course, Doctor.
-What the hell happened?

23:05.080 --> 23:06.380
He said that
he had the flu.

23:06.380 --> 23:08.040
I mean, I told him to go home,
but what is it?

23:08.040 --> 23:10.250
Is it pneumonia? A P.E.?
What happened to him?!

23:10.250 --> 23:13.000
He was injected with a paralytic
by mistake in surgery.

23:13.920 --> 23:14.920
[ Monitor beeping ]

23:14.920 --> 23:16.880
Oh.

23:16.880 --> 23:18.880
Um...
That's, uh...

23:18.880 --> 23:20.290
I'm watching him.

23:20.290 --> 23:22.540
I promise, I'll make sure
he comes through.

23:22.540 --> 23:24.710
Respectfully,
I'm not going anywhere.

23:24.710 --> 23:25.790
Hey.

23:27.960 --> 23:29.380
What?

23:29.380 --> 23:31.170
No one has ever started
a sentence to me

23:31.170 --> 23:32.920
with the word
"respectfully."

23:35.620 --> 23:36.880
Woman on P.A.:
Dr. Ryan to Oncology.

23:36.880 --> 23:38.170
Dr. Ryan to Oncology.

23:38.170 --> 23:39.250
Meredith:
Yeah, no. I get it.

23:39.250 --> 23:40.790
Thank you. Thanks.

23:40.790 --> 23:42.750
[ Cellphone beeps ]

23:42.750 --> 23:45.000
Everything okay?
No.

23:45.000 --> 23:47.210
I have a bunch of 5-year-olds
on their way to my house

23:47.210 --> 23:49.330
for a birthday party,
and Hulk just canceled.

23:49.330 --> 23:50.420
The Hulk.

23:50.420 --> 23:52.080
What?

23:52.080 --> 23:54.290
It's "The Hulk,"
not "Hulk."

23:55.710 --> 23:57.170
Whatever.

23:58.420 --> 23:59.460
I could help.

24:00.960 --> 24:02.290
Seriously?

24:02.290 --> 24:03.750
After the day we just had,
I could use a party.

24:03.750 --> 24:05.290
For 5-year-olds?

24:05.290 --> 24:06.710
I was a Cub Scout.

24:06.710 --> 24:08.420
I make a mean s'more.

24:08.420 --> 24:10.500
But, I mean, if you don't
need the help...

24:10.500 --> 24:11.500
No, wait.

24:11.500 --> 24:13.290
[ Elevator bell dings ]

24:13.290 --> 24:14.750
I'll take the help.

24:14.750 --> 24:16.380
[ Monitor beeping,
respirator hissing ]

24:16.380 --> 24:18.210
[ Liquid suctioning ]

24:21.790 --> 24:24.580
Something wrong?

24:24.580 --> 24:27.000
Tissue's too friable.

24:27.000 --> 24:28.330
Can I help?

24:28.330 --> 24:31.460
You can stop talking
so I can hear myself think.

24:31.460 --> 24:34.620
[ Aron Wright's
"Scared to Love" plays ]

24:34.620 --> 24:36.290
[ Sighs ]

24:36.290 --> 24:39.380
[ Exhales sharply ]
She's incredible.

24:39.380 --> 24:41.380
Hmm, if by "incredible,"
you mean she possesses

24:41.380 --> 24:42.790
an absurd level
of stubbornness,

24:42.790 --> 24:46.210
then, yeah,
she is incredible.

24:46.210 --> 24:47.500
♪ Be yourself ♪
She's only out-stubborned

24:47.500 --> 24:49.750
by the other two people
operating with her.

24:49.750 --> 24:52.580
♪ Be nothing less ♪

24:52.580 --> 24:56.750
♪ Make your choice ♪
I'm, um, trying to be better
about expressing my feelings.

24:56.750 --> 24:59.750
♪ And let it rest ♪
I never asked you to.

24:59.750 --> 25:01.830
♪ When you're looking
for a meaning ♪
Jackson did.

25:01.830 --> 25:03.920
Now he's sharing nothing
about his feelings with me

25:03.920 --> 25:05.170
or with Catherine.

25:05.170 --> 25:06.000
♪ When you're lost
in the haze ♪

25:06.000 --> 25:07.540
Neither is Richard,

25:07.540 --> 25:09.620
and who knows what's going on
in Catherine's head?

25:09.620 --> 25:11.710
♪ In yourself is the healing ♪
They are stubborn.

25:11.710 --> 25:13.290
♪ Be the choices you've made ♪
My mother did the same thing.

25:15.580 --> 25:17.500
She hid her cancer from me,
tried to protect me,

25:17.500 --> 25:20.290
and all I can think of is
how much time we lost.

25:20.290 --> 25:22.330
♪ How you going to know
what you're looking for? ♪

25:22.330 --> 25:24.750
And they could have that time
if they just talked.

25:24.750 --> 25:28.250
So you want them to
hug it all out right now

25:28.250 --> 25:30.290
over an open abdomen?

25:30.290 --> 25:32.830
I'm saying you can
waste a lot of time

25:32.830 --> 25:35.170
waiting for
the right moment.

25:35.170 --> 25:37.170
That storm's gonna come
when it comes.

25:37.170 --> 25:38.710
♪ And I'm scared to love ♪

25:38.710 --> 25:40.710
How can you
just accept that?

25:40.710 --> 25:42.380
♪ You're scared to love ♪

25:42.380 --> 25:45.540
I'm trying to be better

25:45.540 --> 25:47.830
about not trying to control
the things I can't.

25:47.830 --> 25:49.210
♪ Here we are, here we are ♪

25:49.210 --> 25:52.750
♪ Just a little life
on a spinning rock ♪

25:52.750 --> 25:56.000
♪ And you're scared to love ♪
Catherine: Wipes.

25:56.000 --> 25:58.290
♪ I'm scared to love ♪

25:58.290 --> 26:00.170
[ Monitor beeping,
liquid suctioning ]

26:00.170 --> 26:02.500
Hemostat, quickly.

26:02.500 --> 26:05.040
♪♪

26:05.040 --> 26:07.920
Mom, if you're in pain,
I can take over. It's fine.

26:07.920 --> 26:09.580
Yes, Jackson, I'm in pain.

26:09.580 --> 26:12.460
I'm in pain because,
when this woman wakes up,

26:12.460 --> 26:14.080
she will not have
a uterus.

26:14.080 --> 26:15.920
The radiation
has fried her tissues.

26:15.920 --> 26:17.750
It's falling apart
in my hands.

26:17.750 --> 26:19.250
No matter
how many times I try,

26:19.250 --> 26:21.880
I cannot safely
separate the uterus

26:21.880 --> 26:24.080
without compromising
the blood supply.

26:24.080 --> 26:27.210
It's literally disintegrating
right before my eyes.

26:27.210 --> 26:29.460
Her body's been through
too much.

26:29.460 --> 26:30.830
[ Sighs ]

26:30.830 --> 26:32.120
You can't fix that.

26:32.120 --> 26:34.500
Neither can I.
Okay.

26:34.500 --> 26:35.750
No one can fix this.

26:35.750 --> 26:38.420
♪ Scared to love,
scared to love ♪

26:38.420 --> 26:40.540
♪ Scared to love,
scared to love ♪

26:40.540 --> 26:42.670
[ Sighs ]
I'm taking out the uterus.

26:42.670 --> 26:44.250
Bovie.

26:44.250 --> 26:48.210
♪ Oh ♪

26:48.210 --> 26:50.120
♪ Scared to love,
scared to love ♪

26:50.120 --> 26:51.420
Ready?

26:51.420 --> 26:53.330
♪ Scared to love ♪

26:53.330 --> 26:58.080
♪ Scared to love ♪

26:58.080 --> 26:59.710
Close her up.

26:59.710 --> 27:01.420
♪♪

27:01.420 --> 27:03.710
[ Beeping, suctioning continue ]

27:03.710 --> 27:05.710
♪♪

27:11.750 --> 27:14.380
-Hunt was given paralytics?
-Yes, but it was a mistake,

27:14.380 --> 27:16.670
and we got him intubated
and off to a room.

27:16.670 --> 27:18.880
And I've also isolated
the area of perforation

27:18.880 --> 27:20.330
and washed her out.

27:20.330 --> 27:22.750
All right. Right.
Since it's toxic megacolon,

27:22.750 --> 27:26.040
you're gonna have to --
Perform a subtotal colectomy
with an ileostomy.

27:26.040 --> 27:27.330
I did that, too.

27:27.330 --> 27:29.330
All right, so,
what's left?

27:29.330 --> 27:32.210
[ Monitor beeping,
respirator hissing ]

27:32.210 --> 27:34.670
[ Sighs ] I...
I don't know.

27:34.670 --> 27:35.960
You don't know.

27:35.960 --> 27:37.750
It's my first time, okay?

27:37.750 --> 27:40.170
Can you just tell me
what to do next?

27:40.170 --> 27:41.880
You don't know because
there's nothing left.

27:41.880 --> 27:43.170
You did it.

27:43.170 --> 27:45.250
You stepped up.

27:45.250 --> 27:48.210
All right, well, don't get
too swelled up about it.

27:48.210 --> 27:50.460
But great work.
Good job.

27:50.460 --> 27:51.710
Close.

27:51.710 --> 27:56.420
♪♪

27:56.420 --> 27:57.920
[ Coughing ]
Teddy: Okay, all right.

27:57.920 --> 27:59.080
Breathe, breathe.
There you go.

27:59.080 --> 28:00.670
All right. All right.
Okay. Breathe.

28:00.670 --> 28:03.420
Welcome back, Dr. Hunt.
Ugh.

28:03.420 --> 28:05.620
Dr. DeLuca finished
Claire's surgery.

28:05.620 --> 28:08.120
They did the subtotal colectomy,
and she's in recovery now.

28:08.120 --> 28:09.750
[ Hoarsely ]
Oh, great. Thank you.

28:09.750 --> 28:11.420
And thank you
for not dying.

28:11.420 --> 28:12.880
[ Chuckles ]
Okay, we're done.

28:12.880 --> 28:14.210
Thank you, Doctor...

28:14.210 --> 28:16.080
Schmitt, but everybody
calls me --

28:16.080 --> 28:18.380
[ Monitor beeping ]

28:18.380 --> 28:20.460
You know what? No.
Just Dr. Schmitt.

28:20.460 --> 28:21.880
[ Clears throat lightly ]

28:21.880 --> 28:23.290
[ Clatters ]

28:23.290 --> 28:24.460
[ Beeping continues ]

28:24.460 --> 28:26.380
Ohh.
How you feeling?

28:26.380 --> 28:28.250
Ugh, like I got hit
with a brick.

28:28.250 --> 28:30.040
[ Chuckles weakly ]

28:30.040 --> 28:31.460
How was your first day
with Pierce?

28:31.460 --> 28:33.000
[ Chuckles ]

28:33.000 --> 28:34.330
Yeah, well...
[ Sniffs ]

28:34.330 --> 28:36.880
She is Amelia's sister,
so...

28:36.880 --> 28:39.120
[ Ice crunches ]

28:39.120 --> 28:40.960
All right,
you know what? Um...

28:40.960 --> 28:42.460
[ Chair wheels rolling ]

28:45.000 --> 28:46.170
Listen.

28:47.920 --> 28:49.500
I didn't do anything
to Amelia.

28:49.500 --> 28:51.380
I didn't -- I didn't set out
to hurt anyone,

28:51.380 --> 28:53.330
and I know that I'm --
I'm not perfect,

28:53.330 --> 28:56.080
and I have made
plenty of mistakes here,

28:56.080 --> 28:58.750
but you showed up
in Germany,

28:58.750 --> 29:00.580
and then you came back here,
and you did what you did,

29:00.580 --> 29:04.120
so please just stop making
everything my fault.

29:04.120 --> 29:06.250
Landstuhl
was my perfect job.

29:06.250 --> 29:08.830
I was in charge,
I was respected,

29:08.830 --> 29:11.540
and they've not yet
filled that position,

29:11.540 --> 29:13.960
and in Germany,
the maternity leave is --

29:13.960 --> 29:15.290
is really generous.

29:17.540 --> 29:20.880
You -- You -- Are you saying
you want to go back?

29:20.880 --> 29:23.380
I'm saying I'm having a hard
time wanting to stay here

29:23.380 --> 29:25.580
and answer to a 20-something
who hates me.

29:25.580 --> 29:28.040
I'm saying I don't understand
why I'm the only one

29:28.040 --> 29:31.670
who has to sacrifice anything
so that our kid has two parents.

29:31.670 --> 29:32.920
I mean...
[ Sighs ]

29:32.920 --> 29:34.250
...you could move
to Germany.

29:34.250 --> 29:36.750
They've got a great
paternity leave there, too.

29:36.750 --> 29:38.710
[ Beeping continues ]

29:41.620 --> 29:43.210
Stay here.
Work in Trauma.

29:43.210 --> 29:44.790
I don't want
to work for you, Owen.

29:44.790 --> 29:46.420
-Are you even listening to me?
-No, no.

29:46.420 --> 29:48.290
I'm saying...

29:48.290 --> 29:49.580
run the department.

29:49.580 --> 29:50.580
I'll work for you.

29:50.580 --> 29:51.880
I mean,
you're more than qualified,

29:51.880 --> 29:54.750
and we still have a position
that we haven't filled,

29:54.750 --> 29:56.670
and -- and you're right.

29:56.670 --> 29:58.750
Teddy...

29:58.750 --> 30:01.290
you sacrificed a lot
to come here,

30:01.290 --> 30:03.580
and now...

30:03.580 --> 30:05.420
now it is my turn.

30:05.420 --> 30:08.000
Are you giving me
your job?

30:08.000 --> 30:09.080
Teddy...

30:12.290 --> 30:14.420
[ Quietly ] You're
giving me a lot more.

30:14.420 --> 30:16.710
[ Sighs ]

30:16.710 --> 30:19.920
[ Waldeck's
"Keep My Fire Burning" plays ]

30:19.920 --> 30:22.040
♪ Who will keep
my fire burning? ♪

30:22.040 --> 30:23.620
♪♪

30:23.620 --> 30:25.380
♪ Keep my heart yearning? ♪

30:25.380 --> 30:26.540
♪♪

30:26.540 --> 30:28.620
♪ Who will keep
my fire burning? ♪

30:28.620 --> 30:30.290
♪♪

30:30.290 --> 30:31.830
♪ Keep my wheels turning? ♪

30:31.830 --> 30:34.580
♪♪

30:34.580 --> 30:37.290
♪ One, two, three,
wait a second for me ♪

30:37.290 --> 30:40.250
♪ And tell me,
where's my man? ♪

30:40.250 --> 30:43.420
♪ Who will set my soul
on fire? ♪

30:43.420 --> 30:45.710
♪ And feed my desire? ♪
Uh, hi.

30:45.710 --> 30:48.540
I saved
Dr. Hunt's life today.

30:48.540 --> 30:51.250
♪ Who will knock at my door? ♪
I wasn't Glasses.

30:51.250 --> 30:52.420
♪ And make me beg for more? ♪
I wasn't bumbly.

30:52.420 --> 30:54.710
I didn't drop anything.

30:54.710 --> 30:57.500
♪ One, two, three,
wait a second for me ♪
I...felt like
a different person.

30:57.500 --> 30:58.500
[ Breathing heavily ]

30:58.500 --> 31:00.170
♪ Tell me, where's my man? ♪

31:00.170 --> 31:01.620
♪ Who will keep
my fire burning? ♪
I think it's you.

31:01.620 --> 31:04.380
I think you're
rubbing off on me.

31:04.380 --> 31:07.210
♪ Keep my heart yearning? ♪
Or, uh, you know, something
that sounds less dirty.

31:07.210 --> 31:10.790
♪ Who will keep
my fire burning? ♪
I think this has
always been you, and...

31:10.790 --> 31:12.330
you just didn't know it.
♪ Keep my wheels turning? ♪

31:12.330 --> 31:15.170
[ Exhales sharply ]

31:15.170 --> 31:18.540
♪ One, two, three,
wait a second for me ♪

31:18.540 --> 31:21.960
♪ One, two, three,
wait a second for me ♪

31:21.960 --> 31:24.750
♪ One, two, three,
wait a second for me ♪

31:24.750 --> 31:27.120
♪ Tell me, where's my man? ♪

31:27.120 --> 31:28.880
You saved my life.

31:28.880 --> 31:31.000
Thank you for doing this.

31:31.000 --> 31:32.880
You really don't
have to keep saying that.

31:32.880 --> 31:34.880
I'm happy to help.

31:34.880 --> 31:37.460
You seemed kind of...
stressed.

31:37.460 --> 31:38.830
Thought you didn't believe
in stress.

31:38.830 --> 31:40.250
I believe it exists.

31:40.250 --> 31:42.830
I just don't believe
in letting it run your life.

31:42.830 --> 31:45.670
I mean, spending your childhood
in a hospital,

31:45.670 --> 31:47.040
losing half the friends
you made there

31:47.040 --> 31:48.880
to a cancer you survived,

31:48.880 --> 31:50.420
watching your parents
split up

31:50.420 --> 31:53.170
because they could barely
afford your treatments...

31:53.170 --> 31:55.460
made me kind of picky
about what I let get to me.

31:56.540 --> 31:58.290
Dude!

31:58.290 --> 31:59.460
Look at this place!
[ Laughs ]

31:59.460 --> 32:01.620
We did this in, like,
a half an hour.

32:03.080 --> 32:04.920
And I was an ass
to you all day.

32:04.920 --> 32:07.170
I literally did nothing
to deserve this.

32:07.170 --> 32:09.040
[ Sighs ] True.

32:09.040 --> 32:12.290
But...I think I kind of
like the chase.

32:12.290 --> 32:13.460
[ Taps lightly ]

32:13.460 --> 32:14.790
[ Dog barking in distance ]

32:14.790 --> 32:17.080
Because women just
throw themselves at you?

32:17.080 --> 32:20.080
That's not a phrase
I would ever use.
[ Door opens ]

32:20.080 --> 32:21.830
Ready or not,
here we are!

32:21.830 --> 32:24.920
-Hello!
-Happy birthday, Bailey!

32:24.920 --> 32:26.830
-[ Chuckling ] All right!
-[ Laughs ]

32:26.830 --> 32:28.880
What do you think?

32:28.880 --> 32:30.250
Come on, you guys!
Hey!

32:30.250 --> 32:31.000
Presents go
right over there.

32:31.000 --> 32:32.580
Wait.

32:32.580 --> 32:34.830
Are you Thor?

32:34.830 --> 32:36.880
I am.

32:36.880 --> 32:38.380
So cool!

32:38.380 --> 32:40.830
Now, which one of you kids
stole my hammer?

32:40.830 --> 32:42.210
Aah!
[ Laughter ]

32:42.210 --> 32:45.210
[ All shouting ]

32:45.210 --> 32:46.620
[ Laughter ]

32:46.620 --> 32:52.210
♪♪

32:55.830 --> 32:57.620
I completed the ostomies,

32:57.620 --> 33:00.120
and Jackson closed
with a flap.

33:00.120 --> 33:02.000
Uma's in recovery.

33:02.000 --> 33:03.330
How is she doing?

33:04.960 --> 33:06.500
[ Sighs ]
Stable.

33:12.290 --> 33:13.580
Now, look, Mom, I know
you're frustrated, okay?

33:13.580 --> 33:14.710
Frustrated?

33:14.710 --> 33:16.880
I'm livid.

33:16.880 --> 33:19.120
You questioned my ability
to complete that surgery.

33:19.120 --> 33:21.420
You inferred that
I am somehow not capable --

33:21.420 --> 33:23.460
You had a massive tumor
on your spine,

33:23.460 --> 33:25.120
and you didn't say
anything about it.
[ Scoffs ]

33:25.120 --> 33:26.750
You didn't even tell me
you had cancer.

33:26.750 --> 33:28.620
I wasn't ready
to bring anyone else into it.

33:28.620 --> 33:30.120
Except you did.

33:30.120 --> 33:33.000
You told Maggie.
I did not tell Maggie.

33:33.000 --> 33:35.040
I told Meredith.
Right. That's different.

33:35.040 --> 33:37.210
Tom Koracick.

33:37.210 --> 33:39.380
I see.
Just the important people.

33:39.380 --> 33:40.920
-I told people who could help.
-Wow.

33:40.920 --> 33:42.420
Good Lord,
that's offensive.

33:42.420 --> 33:44.380
Do you have any idea
what that sounds like?
Richard, please.

33:44.380 --> 33:45.620
How am I supposed to
depend on you

33:45.620 --> 33:48.540
when you're hanging out in bars,
swinging baseball bats?

33:48.540 --> 33:50.210
No, no, now, that's
not his business...
Wait, what?

33:50.210 --> 33:51.920
...and that's not what
we're talking about.

33:51.920 --> 33:54.460
You all are acting like
such big old babies.

33:54.460 --> 33:56.790
This is my problem!
Oh, the hell it is.

33:56.790 --> 33:58.750
No more than my first wife's
Alzheimer's was her problem.

33:58.750 --> 34:00.670
This is all our problems,
Catherine.
No, no.

34:00.670 --> 34:02.290
You do not want
to go in there.
Sorry. Wait.
Can we go back?

34:02.290 --> 34:04.960
There's a --
a big storm in there.
What happened at the bar?

34:04.960 --> 34:06.880
A big, big storm.
They were giving people shots
for their AA chips.

34:06.880 --> 34:07.750
Are you serious?
That's disgusting.

34:07.750 --> 34:09.120
Amen.

34:09.120 --> 34:11.380
Stop it. Stop it.
Stop it!

34:11.380 --> 34:14.580
Now, I was not wrong
not to tell you.

34:14.580 --> 34:17.000
You were --
This is what you always do.

34:17.000 --> 34:18.580
It's exactly
what you always do --

34:18.580 --> 34:19.540
now, you try to control
everyone and everything

34:19.540 --> 34:20.580
that you're around.

34:20.580 --> 34:22.170
And look what happens
when I don't.

34:22.170 --> 34:24.290
I'm gone for two days,
and my husband

34:24.290 --> 34:26.620
has an arrest record.
I'm married to a felon.

34:26.620 --> 34:27.830
Mom, he just said they
were trying to give shots

34:27.830 --> 34:29.080
to people with AA chips.

34:29.080 --> 34:30.580
I would've smashed
the damn place up myself.

34:30.580 --> 34:32.710
Thank you.
Uh, I mean, that --

34:32.710 --> 34:35.120
that's -- that's still, uh,
no -- no excuse for my behavior.

34:35.120 --> 34:37.580
I mean, I realize
that now, but...

34:37.580 --> 34:39.710
We can handle bad news,
all right?

34:39.710 --> 34:41.120
We're surgeons.

34:41.120 --> 34:43.080
And we're your family.
[ Sighs ]

34:43.080 --> 34:44.460
We deserve the truth.

34:44.460 --> 34:46.420
You two both know if
I had told you any sooner

34:46.420 --> 34:47.710
you would've
driven me crazy,

34:47.710 --> 34:49.880
ordering every test
under the sun.

34:49.880 --> 34:51.040
At least Thomas --

34:51.040 --> 34:52.290
Don't -- Don't say
that man's name again.

34:52.290 --> 34:53.880
Richard, honestly,
your jealousy

34:53.880 --> 34:55.460
is your least attractive
quality.

34:55.460 --> 34:57.290
And lying doesn't look very good
on you, either, Catherine.

34:57.290 --> 34:58.790
No, you don't get
to say that to me.

34:58.790 --> 35:00.670
You don't get
to talk to me like that!

35:00.670 --> 35:02.250
Not now, not with all
that I'm going through!

35:02.250 --> 35:03.460
Mom, you're seriously
gonna play --

35:03.460 --> 35:06.120
Play the cancer card?
You're damn skippy.

35:06.120 --> 35:08.920
And I'll be irrational,
and I'll make bad decisions,

35:08.920 --> 35:11.750
and I can play
the cancer card all I want,

35:11.750 --> 35:13.790
because I'm the one
with the damn cancer!

35:16.330 --> 35:18.460
[ Voice breaking ]
And talking to both of you

35:18.460 --> 35:20.080
makes it true.

35:20.080 --> 35:23.040
♪♪

35:23.040 --> 35:24.880
Hey. Hey.

35:24.880 --> 35:28.460
[ Crying ]

35:28.460 --> 35:30.500
♪♪

35:36.540 --> 35:39.460
But, luckily, Dr. DeLuca
was here to take over for me.

35:39.460 --> 35:42.080
Wow. I wish
I could've seen that.
Mm.

35:42.080 --> 35:45.420
Are you okay?

35:45.420 --> 35:46.710
We're sorry.

35:46.710 --> 35:48.080
For what?

35:49.080 --> 35:50.540
You don't have to
be sorry.

35:50.540 --> 35:53.790
Today was
a really scary day.

35:53.790 --> 35:57.210
And I'm gonna need both of you
to help me for a little while.

35:57.210 --> 35:59.000
You can start
by going into my wallet,

35:59.000 --> 36:01.580
getting some money,
getting yourself some pizza.

36:01.580 --> 36:04.170
Aunt Claire is starving,
so save me some.

36:04.170 --> 36:05.920
Yes, ma'am.
Okay.

36:05.920 --> 36:07.960
-You can't eat, Claire.
-Shh.

36:07.960 --> 36:09.380
[ Inhales deeply ]

36:09.380 --> 36:10.880
It makes them
feel better to help.

36:10.880 --> 36:13.290
[ Sighs ]

36:13.290 --> 36:16.250
Ohh, I can't believe
I almost died.

36:16.250 --> 36:18.710
Well, you were
in good hands.

36:18.710 --> 36:21.080
Thank you
for saving my life.

36:21.080 --> 36:22.830
You're very welcome.

36:22.830 --> 36:25.330
And you.
♪ Take it in ♪

36:25.330 --> 36:27.500
Thank you
for making me stay.

36:27.500 --> 36:31.380
♪ While you can ♪
Yeah.

36:31.380 --> 36:37.620
♪ On the edge of it all ♪

36:37.620 --> 36:39.460
♪♪

36:39.460 --> 36:43.580
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

36:43.580 --> 36:48.710
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

36:48.710 --> 36:50.790
♪♪

36:50.790 --> 36:55.080
♪ I feel it coming ♪

36:55.080 --> 36:59.250
♪ Hold your breath ♪

36:59.250 --> 37:03.460
♪ Don't let go ♪

37:03.460 --> 37:06.880
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

37:06.880 --> 37:11.380
♪ I feel it coming ♪

37:11.380 --> 37:12.830
♪ Hold your breath ♪

37:12.830 --> 37:14.040
[ Panting ]

37:14.040 --> 37:16.580
Hey. Hey.

37:16.580 --> 37:18.670
Honestly, Owen,
I'm -- I'm too tired.

37:18.670 --> 37:21.040
I gave Teddy my job.

37:21.040 --> 37:23.620
Okay.
Yeah.

37:23.620 --> 37:26.290
'Cause I want her to stay.

37:26.290 --> 37:28.710
I want her here.
I want the baby here.

37:28.710 --> 37:31.580
[ Breathes sharply ]
Clearly.

37:31.580 --> 37:33.420
It's the truth, Amelia,

37:33.420 --> 37:35.460
and I have to be able
to tell you the truth.

37:35.460 --> 37:36.580
I have to be able
to make mistakes,

37:36.580 --> 37:38.500
because there is
no clear path here.

37:38.500 --> 37:40.120
The only thing
I know for sure

37:40.120 --> 37:42.210
is that I am having
a baby with Teddy

37:42.210 --> 37:44.500
and that I have a very real
family with you,

37:44.500 --> 37:47.580
and I don't want to do
any of it without you.

37:47.580 --> 37:49.790
I miss you.

37:49.790 --> 37:51.210
I miss us.

37:51.210 --> 37:54.960
♪ On the edge of it all ♪

37:54.960 --> 37:57.710
♪ Take it in ♪
I don't need time.

37:59.380 --> 38:03.210
♪ While you can ♪
I need you.

38:03.210 --> 38:06.960
♪ On the edge ♪
[ Sighs ]

38:06.960 --> 38:10.670
♪ Of it all ♪

38:10.670 --> 38:11.750
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪

38:11.750 --> 38:15.290
What took you so long?

38:15.290 --> 38:18.330
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh ♪
I was paralyzed.

38:18.330 --> 38:20.380
Seriously --
No, literally.

38:20.380 --> 38:21.880
What?
Yeah, it was weird.
It was...

38:21.880 --> 38:23.080
Are you...
Yeah.

38:23.080 --> 38:26.790
♪ I feel it coming ♪
It was, like...

38:29.120 --> 38:31.040
[ Telephone rings
in distance ]

38:34.250 --> 38:35.880
What?

38:35.880 --> 38:37.710
Cheat Day. [ Chuckles ]

38:37.710 --> 38:39.580
Mm...

38:39.580 --> 38:42.040
You're about, what,
16 weeks, right?

38:43.580 --> 38:44.880
Do you work
for a carnival?

38:44.880 --> 38:46.920
Every other week.
Want a ticket?

38:46.920 --> 38:48.120
[ Chuckles ]

38:48.120 --> 38:49.330
I'm Tom.

38:49.330 --> 38:50.920
I'm sorry.

38:50.920 --> 38:53.500
I can't hear you over
the smell of those fries.

38:53.500 --> 38:55.420
Oh, here.

38:57.580 --> 38:58.880
Here. Do your worst.

39:00.380 --> 39:01.920
I have feet on my hands.

39:01.920 --> 39:03.620
I'm not gonna feed you
unless I have to.

39:03.620 --> 39:05.120
I don't even know you.
Well, that's on you.

39:05.120 --> 39:06.330
I tried
to introduce myself.

39:06.330 --> 39:08.710
Teddy Altman.
New Chief of Trauma.

39:08.710 --> 39:09.750
I know.

39:09.750 --> 39:11.880
Tom Koracick,
world-renowned neurosurgeon.

39:11.880 --> 39:13.170
Oh.
We good?

39:13.170 --> 39:15.170
Better.
Hmm.

39:15.170 --> 39:16.830
You really want one,
don't you?

39:16.830 --> 39:18.580
I really do.
Yeah.

39:18.580 --> 39:20.250
[ Chuckles ] Here.

39:20.250 --> 39:21.790
[ Crunching ] Mmm!

39:21.790 --> 39:23.830
Meredith:
Help comes in many forms.

39:23.830 --> 39:24.960
Mm-hmm.
All right.

39:24.960 --> 39:27.210
A kidney, a kind gesture,

39:27.210 --> 39:28.920
a friend to light your way.

39:28.920 --> 39:30.580
♪♪

39:30.580 --> 39:31.670
[ Groans ]

39:31.670 --> 39:33.670
Still...

39:33.670 --> 39:36.120
too often we insist
on doing it ourselves.

39:36.120 --> 39:39.380
♪ You're angry, but you
don't know how to be that yet ♪

39:39.380 --> 39:40.830
What's he doing?

39:40.830 --> 39:42.330
Casey: Trying to touch
his eyeball.

39:42.330 --> 39:43.460
Why?

39:43.460 --> 39:46.540
Because I want to look
as different as I feel.

39:46.540 --> 39:49.250
♪♪

39:49.250 --> 39:50.170
♪ Resistance
seems impossible... ♪

39:50.170 --> 39:51.290
Ugh.

39:51.290 --> 39:53.170
Do you want me to do it?
Yes, please.

39:53.170 --> 39:55.540
♪ ...from down this low ♪
[ Chuckles ]

39:55.540 --> 39:58.380
We're afraid of looking weak,

39:58.380 --> 39:59.710
of not being tough.

39:59.710 --> 40:01.790
♪ And surely no one else
can feel like this ♪

40:01.790 --> 40:03.790
[ Laughs ]
Truth is,
we're all capable

40:03.790 --> 40:05.790
of walking through the world
by ourselves.

40:05.790 --> 40:07.580
Link: I take it back.

40:07.580 --> 40:10.170
What?
I don't blame you
for being stressed.

40:10.170 --> 40:11.830
[ Chuckles ]
Three kids is no joke.

40:11.830 --> 40:13.790
[ Sighs loudly ]
And you run a department,

40:13.790 --> 40:15.170
win awards.

40:15.170 --> 40:17.460
I'm shocked you're not
more stressed.

40:17.460 --> 40:19.170
Well, trust me --

40:19.170 --> 40:20.920
I'm having a glass of wine
with Thor,

40:20.920 --> 40:22.080
and all I'm doing is
thinking about

40:22.080 --> 40:24.880
how much stuff
I have to do tomorrow.

40:24.880 --> 40:26.330
♪ Sound and pulse
and volume ♪

40:26.330 --> 40:28.460
What?

40:28.460 --> 40:29.710
You like me.

40:29.710 --> 40:31.380
I don't dislike you.

40:31.380 --> 40:34.460
[ Both laugh ]

40:34.460 --> 40:37.210
Which is an improvement
from this morning, right?

40:37.210 --> 40:39.080
[ Chuckles ]
[ Cellphone chimes, vibrates ]

40:39.080 --> 40:41.210
I won't be offended
if you have to check that.

40:41.210 --> 40:43.040
I'm gonna give myself
a moment.

40:43.040 --> 40:44.080
♪ This is so damn simple,
yeah ♪

40:44.080 --> 40:46.500
♪ It's so damn simple ♪

40:46.500 --> 40:49.460
I have figured out
why you run so much, though.

40:49.460 --> 40:52.330
You eat more junk food
than any surgeon I've ever met.

40:52.330 --> 40:55.620
One perk of being
a cancer kid --

40:55.620 --> 40:58.040
I get to eat
whatever I want,

40:58.040 --> 41:00.170
and no one
can tell me no.

41:00.170 --> 41:02.120
[ Laughs ]
♪ This is so damn simple ♪

41:04.960 --> 41:06.500
Yes!
But most of the time,

41:06.500 --> 41:08.170
life is better with company.
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

41:08.170 --> 41:12.290
♪♪

41:13.080 --> 41:14.460
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

41:14.460 --> 41:15.290
[ Laughs ]

41:29.210 --> 41:37.420
♪♪

41:37.420 --> 41:45.580
♪♪

41:45.580 --> 41:54.210
♪♪
